<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this warm-up is to allow students to connect language to mathematical representation, which will be useful when students need to compare quantities and numbers in later activities. In the synthesis, students have the opportunity to practice using the language <q>more</q> to compare quantities. </p>
<p>This warm-up gives students opportunities to make sense of a problem by acting it out first before thinking about how to solve the problem (MP1).</p>
  </paragraphs>

